        {
            "chunk_index": 7,
            "text": "SEC. 3.\n\nConduct and Supervision of Plebiscite.\n\n- The plebiscite conducted and supervised by the Commission on Elections (COMELEC) on March 14, 1993 pursuant to Provincial Ordinance No. 2, Series of 1991, dated September 5, 1991 of the Sangguniang Panlalawigan of the Province of Tarlac, which ratified the creation of Barangay Care, shall serve as substantial compliance with the plebiscite requirement under Section 10 of Republic Act No. 7160, as amended, otherwise known as the \"Local Government Code of 1991\".\n\nSEC. 4.\n\nIncumbent Barangay Officials.\n\n- The incumbent barangay officials of barangay care shall continue to hold office until such time that their successors have been duly elected and qualified.\n\nSEC. 5.\n\nPublic Infrastructure and Facilities.\n\n- All public infrastructure and facilities for public use existing therein at the time of the approval of this Act are hereby transferred without cost or compensation to and shall be administered by the new barangay.",
            "metadata": {
                "law_id": "RA_10956",
                "date": "October 30, 2017"
            }
        },
        {
            "chunk_index": 8,
            "text": "SEC. 6.\n\nInternal Revenue Allotment Shares.\n\n- Barangay Care shall be entitled to Internal Revenue Allotment (IRA) shares pursuant to Section 285 of Republic Act No. 7160, as amended, otherwise known as the \"Local Government Code of 1991\".\n\nSEC. 7.\n\nEffectivity.\n\n- This Act shall take effect fifteen (15) days after its publication in the\n\nOfficial Gazette\n\nor in a newspaper of general circulation.\n\nApproved,\n\n(SGD.)\n\nAQUILINO \"KOKO\" PIMENTEL III\n\nPresident of the Senate\n\n(SGD.)\n\nPANTALEON D. ALVAREZ\n\nSpeaker of the House of Representatives\n\nThis Act which originated in the House of Representatives was passed by the House of Representatives on March 13, 2017, amended by the Senate on August 14, 2017, and which amendments were concurred in by the House of Representatives on August 30, 2017.\n\n(SGD.)\n\nLUTGARDO B. BARBO\n\nSecretary of the Senate\n\n(SGD.)\n\nCESAR STRAIT PAREJA\n\nSecretary General\n\nHouse of Representatives\n\nApproved: OCT 30 2017\n\n(SGD.)\n\nRODRIGO ROA DUTERTE\n\nPresident of the Philippines",
